==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fidget
<hw>Fidg"et</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Fidgeted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Fodgeting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[From <er>Fidge</er>; cf. OE.
<ets>fiken</ets> to fidget, to flatter, Icel. <ets>fika</ets> to hasten,
Sw. <ets>fika</ets> to hunt after, AS. <ets>befician</ets> to deceive.
Cf. <er>Fickle</er>.]</ety> <def>To move uneasily one way and the other;
to move irregularly, or by fits and starts.</def>
<rj><au>Moore.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fidget</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Fidget
<hw>Fidg"et</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Uneasiness;
restlessness.</def> <rj><au>Cowper.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <def>A general nervous restlessness,
manifested by incessant changes of position; dysphoria.</def>
<rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fidgetiness</ent>⟦br⟧
